  "conclusion": "RSA security is geometric distance in rank-trajectory space. R(k,f) encodes factoring as a zero-crossing detection problem. Signal amplitude stays near 1.0 for k << p (never noise-limited). The zero-crossing at k=p requires traversing p ~ 2^512 steps \u2014 classical hardness is distance, not amplitude."
